The third head quae praecepta des occupies the rest of the dialogue its be· ginning being marked by the words ‘Quamobrem id primum videamus’ in 5 36. Three heads are declared by Cornificius (Ad Herennium 1, 5 17) to be the proper number for a speech. But of course the number must vary with the requirements of the subject matter even in ioreusic oratory, and this is still more the case in a philosophical disquisition.
